Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Male' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I go to Page 05 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button

When I select 'Scrotum, cryptorchidism' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left' checkbox is enabled

And 'Intraabdominal' radio button is enabled
And 'Inguinoscrotal' radio button is enabled
And 'Not detectable' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Right' checkbox
Then 'Testicular atrophy' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Left' checkbox
Then 'Testicular atrophy' checkbox is enabled
